<head>BE AT HOME</head>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">在家裡</item>
        <item xml:lang="och">入</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>BE-IN one's SELF:own DWELLING.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>[ACTIVITY/STATE]</p>
<p>[GENERAL/SPECIFIC]</p>
<p>1. The general Confucian term is rù 入 (ant. chū 出 "be abroad") and it refers quite generally to one's not going out or having left chū 出.</p>
<p>[GENERAL], [STATE]</p>
<p>2. Jū 居 (ant. xíng 行 "travel") includes the notion of behaviour at home, one's domestic moral deameanour, and the word often connotes peace, calm, and quiet at home.</p>
<p>[ACTIVITY]</p>
        </div>
